; v0.3 Track C: region-escape convergence case for the evaluation corpus.
;
; `total` builds a vector inside a `region`, but publishes it to `acc` — a
; binding declared *outside* the region — with a `set`. That escapes the region:
; the vector's allocation would outlive the region's arena. The region gate
; rejects it with REGION_ESCAPE, and the only repair is `copy-out`: wrap the
; published value in `copy`. The loop applies it, producing an independent value
; the runtime relocates to the parent frame, so the region becomes arena-managed
; and frees its scratch while `acc` keeps the copy.
;
; `copy` is value-equal to its source, so the oracle is unchanged by the repair.
(module regionescape
  (fn total (params (n i64)) (ret i64)
    (body
      (let acc (vec i64) (vec-new (vec i64))
        (block
          (region r
            (set acc (vec-push (vec-push (ref acc) (ref n)) (ref n))))
          (len (ref acc)))))))
